  "slides": [
    {
      "kicker": "Overview",
      "title": "What You're Making",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "p",
          "html": "Cook farro while you sear seasoned salmon in a hot skillet. Toss the warm grain with raw vegetables and a bright vinaigrette, then top with salmon and pistachios—substantial enough for dinner in under half an hour."
        },
        {
          "type": "spacer"
        },
        {
          "type": "ul",
          "items": [
            "<strong>Simmer farro</strong> until tender, then drain",
            "<strong>Sear salmon</strong> flesh side first, then flip to skin side",
            "<strong>Combine</strong> farro with prepped vegetables and cilantro",
            "<strong>Whisk dressing</strong>, toss through the bowl",
            "<strong>Plate</strong> in shallow bowls → salmon → pistachios"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "html": "<strong>Prep window:</strong> While farro and salmon cook, chop vegetables so everything lands in the bowl at once."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kicker": "Step 1",
      "title": "Cook the Farro",
      "checkboxLabel": "Farro tender, drained",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "ul",
          "items": [
            "Cook farro <strong>according to package directions</strong> (volume of water and time vary by brand).",
            "<strong>Drain</strong> well and set aside."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "html": "<strong>10-minute farro</strong> is handy here; whole farro takes longer but works the same way."
        }
      ],
      "measurements": [
        {
          "item": "Farro",
          "qty": "1 cup dry",
          "alts": ["Pearl barley", "Freekeh"]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kicker": "Step 2",
      "title": "Sear the Salmon",
      "checkboxLabel": "Salmon cooked, flaky, moist",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "ul",
          "items": [
            "Heat <strong>2 tbsp olive oil</strong> in a large skillet over <strong>medium</strong> heat.",
            "<strong>Pat salmon dry.</strong> Season with <strong>salt, pepper, onion powder, and garlic powder</strong>.",
            "Place <strong>flesh-side down</strong> → cook <strong>~4 minutes</strong>.",
            "Flip to <strong>skin side</strong> → cook <strong>~4 minutes more</strong> until it flakes easily but doesn’t look dry.",
            "Transfer to a plate and keep warm if needed."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "html": "<strong>Skinless fillets:</strong> Cook the second side the same way; reduce time slightly if the fish is thin."
        }
      ],
